{"type":"message","id":"528eda3c","parentId":"9f0493a6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:49:48.669Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yid70c81c5gr_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 114815\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- CFI Analysis is complete with findings documented in `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n\r\nPending tasks:\r\n- CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n- Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe most actionable next step is the CFI-weighted compression experiment - this directly follows from the CFI analysis findings.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what this experiment should be:\r\n- Compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline\r\n- Measure next-pulse prediction accuracy or compression quality\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment design document that outlines:\r\n1. The experiment methodology\r\n2. How to implement CFI-weighted compression\r\n3. What metrics to measure\r\n4. The comparison baseline\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: Design the CFI-weighted compression experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) and only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7). This means frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss. The logical next step is designing an experiment to compare CFI-weighted compression against the frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate an experiment design document for the CFI-weighted compression experiment, specifying methodology, implementation approach, and success metrics. This will serve as the blueprint for the actual experiment implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only baseline by filtering out metaprogramming noise (CFI≈0) and prioritizing true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Comparison Conditions\r\n\r\n| Condition | Weighting | Expected Outcome |\r\n|-----------|-----------|------------------|\r\n| **Baseline** | Frequency only (freq=60 for constants) | Overfits to format noise |\r\n| **CFI-Weighted** | freq × CFI (normalized) | Preserves causal structure |\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Prediction Accuracy\r\n\r\n**Methodology:**\r\n1. Extract invariants from N training sessions (discard the session with CFI analysis)\r\n2. Build two compression models:\r\n   - Baseline: `weight = freq`\r\n   - CFI-Weighted: `weight = freq × CFI`\r\n3. For each invariant, predict whether it will persist in next session\r\n4. Compare prediction accuracy vs actual persistence\r\n\r\n### Implementation Steps\r\n\r\n1. **Extract training data:**\r\n   - Parse 10-20 historical pulse files\r\n   - Extract invariants with (frequency, CFI) pairs\r\n   - Label each as \"persisted\" or \"decayed\" in subsequent session\r\n\r\n2. **Build compression models:**\r\n   ```python\r\n   def baseline_weight(freq):\r\n       return freq\r\n\r\n   def cfi_weight(freq, cfi):\r\n       return freq * cfi  # CFI acts as multiplicative filter\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n3. **Evaluate persistence prediction:**\r\n   - Sort invariants by weight descending\r\n   - Take top-K (varying K = 10, 20, 50, 100)\r\n   - Measure: precision@K (how many in top-K actually persisted)\r\n\r\n### Success Criteria\r\n- CFI-Weighted precision@20 > Baseline precision@20 by ≥15%\r\n- Demonstrates that CFI filtering removes metaprogramming contamination\r\n\r\n## Expected Findings\r\n\r\nBased on CFI analysis:\r\n- Baseline will rank \"constant format\" items (freq=60, CFI=1) highest\r\n- CFI-Weighted will rank \"research trajectory\" items (freq<60, CFI>0.7) highest\r\n- Research trajectory items have higher true persistence than format items\r\n\r\n## Next Steps After Experiment\r\n1. If hypothesis confirmed → Implement CFI filtering in production\r\n2. Distinguish constant format (freq=60, CFI=1) from research trajectory (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\r\n3. Add CFI as first-class attribute in invariant tracking\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24*\r\n*Related: research/CFI_RESULTS.md*\r\nfile: research/CFI_EXPERIMENT_DESIGN.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:48:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774367388666}}
